                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Personally, I think using charm for soloing takes some degree of skill, requires total concentration (if hasted, and dual wielding), and has a rather steep learning curve.  As a consequence few charm-solo - at least on Vazaelle.
<br />

<br />
My pets in Tactics or Fire have a healthy DPS of 450-600 range.  Yes I can solo a lot but I die a fair bit too.  I am consistently the only chanter on my server that solos in Tactics or Fire (based on the fact that I have very rarely seen another out there).  Soloing chanters imo are far and few between, to penalise the entire class is wrong because a few people can do things.
<br />

<br />
When a new expansion comes out one would expect the curve to continue to increase (ie 450-600 range to curve up 600-900 DPS range).  Instead, we get hit with something so ridiculous a charmed pet doing &lt;300 DPS yet when charm breaks it is hitting back for normal.  Take into account using a charmed pet in OoW does take some degree of experience from the group  does randomly break and can eat the entire group because it instantly goes back to being the horrid monster it was pre-charm instead of the upgraded animation it really is.
<br />

<br />
I like the power of charming, I like the power of mezzing.  Mezzing has been shite since GoD, so most chanters have fallen onto charming to help with group dynamics..now that has taken a huge blow.  It is time that SoE looks into our class properly.  I rarely bitch or complain but I do feel that the changes made to our class have made it far less fun to play than previously.
<br />

<br />
Regards,
<br />

<br />
Lady Neibruoma Meztress
<br />
66 Enchanter
<br />
Vazaelle</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
