                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">1 - Groups don't want a 260hitting pet eating 33pct(or what ever pct it will turn out to be) of there exp . </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">WHY DOES NOBODY UNDERSTAND THE 33% RULE?!</span>
<br />

<br />
Ok ok.  Here goes.
<br />

<br />
The pet will eat 1/3 of it's damage share.  If it does 10% of the damage, it eats 1/3 of 10% or 3.3% of the xp.  Unless pulls take 2 times longer than killing the mob (without the pet), the pet will increase your xp rate.
<br />

<br />
In effect, drop the mobs's DPS by 33%, and that is now much "DPS-xp" it generates.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Completed Tipt trials with no snare and under 4khp /flex icon_smile.gif Having a great group made the difference. pretty much sums it up, and lvl 8 root is your friend icon_smile.gif</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Stunting is sometimes fun, isn't it?
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I do not even do hard LDON because I find even charming in those zones to easy and boring to do.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Hasted (with item haste, VSB or Jumpy) DWing LDoN hard mobs are easy?
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">An unhasted pets dps is so low that the small amount of extra experience is really not worth the extra work in keeping the pet charmed,</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Unhasted LDoN hard mobs are worth keeping around if you lack group utility to buff them fully.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Mezzing isn't something enchanters are good at anymore.  Really.  On a resist, we are reduced to poor kiters (on faster-than-us OoW mobs), because enchanters are not itemized with gear that lets us tank mobs which are a challenge to a plate class on a simular level of gear.
<br />

<br />
We aren't charmers, because we have to tank the mob when charm breaks, short of building groups with charm support.  Charm DPS has been reduced to the point where it isn't worth building charm-support groups.
<br />

<br />
We are buffers.
<br />

<br />
I guess Rangers lose the one thing that makes them special, Archery.  Enchanters lose the things that make them special.  We get better nukes!  And a higher DPS animation!  WEEE!
<br />

<br />
Does SOE not understand: most enchanters <span style="font-weight: bold">want</span> to crowd control, <span style="font-weight: bold">want</span> to charm mobs and it be worth it.  Delete my nukes.  Screw my animation.  I don't want to be a slow-casting, buffing, gimped pseudo-mage.  Is that what SOE thinks enchanters should be?  I mean it would be easier to balance.  =p~</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
