                        <tr>
                                <td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><a href="viewtopic.php?p=71407#71407"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Tue Sep 21, 2004 2:15 pm<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: </span></td>
                                <td align="right" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=71407"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>    </td></tr></table></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">My point that alot seemed to have missed is that the pet will eat exp and it doesn't matter if its 1pct or 33pct no one is gonna want it in the group period, so say good by to charming.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
And thus proving that you don't understand the 33% rule.
<br />

<br />
The pet will eat 3 times less xp than it generated.
<br />

<br />
A charmed pet will not cost you XP from the XP-theft until your pulls slow to taking 2/3 of the playtime (before you get the charmed pet), or breaks become so bad that they generate more downtime than he helps.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Players get more hitpoints, and mobs get higher dps.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
And players get better at healing that pool of hitpoints.
<br />

<br />
It is cheaper for a L 70 cleric to heal a 15-18 k warrior than it is for a L 20 cleric to heal a L 20 warrior, in terms of casting time and mana regen time.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">With GoD, they simply made flagged most mobs uncharmable. (KT, Qvic?), but they did leave us charmable mobs for the initial content</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
They did this as a hack post-launch.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> When charm breaks when you are using charm as a crowd control tool <span style="font-weight: bold">you are killing the ex-pet as soon as possible</span></td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
But, a zero-resist-modifier charm that takes 5 seconds to cast isn't a viable crowd control choice at higher levels.  Either mez lands trivially, or charm will last so short a time using it on an undebuffed mob is stupid.
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I agree that it's not the smartest point of view, and I think it's going to be a real social problem in OOW with dangerous, low damage charmpets. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
The problem here is the pet wipes the group.  The XP theft is simply further lowering of the pet's effective XP DPS.
<br />

<br />
At 30% of the mob's uncharmed DPS, the pet does 20% of the mob's DPS as XP-DPS.  So the pet does 5 times more DPS on charm breaks as he is "worth" during the non-break periods on mobs.
<br />

<br />
That ratio (XP-DPS to DPS on charm break) is why charm is completely and utterly broken in OoW as a source of DPS for enchanters.
<br />

<br />
The resist rates of charm are why charm is completely and utterly broken in OoW as a source of Crowd Contorl power for enchanters.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
