		<td width="150" align="left" valign="top" class="row2"><a name="71461"></a><span class="name"><span class="usercolor">Somnabulist</span></span><div class="gensmall"><img src="images/ranks/rank_7.gif" alt="Coercer" title="Coercer" border="0" /><br />Coercer</div><div align="center"><img src="images/avatars/database/600avatars/486.gif" alt="Avatar" border="0" /></div><br /><div align="left" class="gensmall">Gender:&nbsp;Male</div></td>
                <td class="row2" width="100%" height="28" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                        <tr>
                                <td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><a href="viewtopic.php?p=71461#71461"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Tue Sep 21, 2004 3:41 pm<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: </span></td>
                                <td align="right" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=71461"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>    </td></tr></table></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">But, a zero-resist-modifier charm that takes 5 seconds to cast isn't a viable crowd control choice at higher levels.  Either mez lands trivially, or charm will last so short a time using it on an undebuffed mob is stupid.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Yakk, when you use charm as a crowd control instead of a DPS provider, you don't cast charm when you need to mez.
<br />

<br />
The only spell line you can use in place of mez in the entire game that will even be as close as effective at that stage of crowd control when a mobs are incoming is Root.  That's it.  Locking down mobs is part of crowd control, not the whole damn thing.
<br />

<br />
OK, let's put it this way.
<br />

<br />
Part of crowd control is prevention.  This is Pacify/Mem Blur.
<br />

<br />
Part of crowd control is by locking down.  That's Mez, Root, and sometimes a nuke or dispel to move a mob elsewhere so that it can be locked down in a not-as-inconvenient spot.
<br />

<br />
And part of crowd control is making it easier to eliminate the crowds.  Tash, Slow, and Charm all go here.
<br />

<br />
Look at it that way instead of just locking down mobs.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Sleeping for 65 nights (with 338 interruptions...)
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=467231" target="_blank" class="postlink">ZZZzzzzzz...</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
